On Wed, 31 Oct 2001, Simon Ramirez Jr. wrote:

> There is a great article on replacing the heater tube (under the bus)
> in the archives.  I think I found it using the search string 'bilge blower'.
>  There are a few ways, one that sounds appealing in the 2" PVC pipe...

Two problems with 2" PVC pipe.

1. too small.
2. PVC was not made to handle the temperatures that the heat exchangers
are capable of producing.  Outgassing problems might rear their ugly
heads.

Better to use a metal duct, close to the same size as the original.
Insulate with fiberglass.

George Lyle

